ens of Norway]]\n[[Category:Nobel Peace Prize laureates]]\n[[Category:Norwegian refugees]]\n[[Category:People from L\u00fcbeck]]\n[[Category:Exiles from Nazi Germany]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the Socialist International]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Order of the White Lion]]\n[[Category:Refugees in Norway]]\n[[Category:Refugees in Sweden]]\n[[Category:Social Democratic Party of Germany politicians]]\n[[Category:Socialist Workers' Party of Germany politicians]]\n[[Category:Vice-Chancellors of Germany]]\n[[Category:War correspondents of the Spanish Civil War]]\n[[Category:Alterspr\u00e4sidents of the Bundestag]]\n[[Category:Grand Crosses 1st class of the Order of Merit of the Federal Republic of Germany]]\n[[Category:Honorary Grand Commanders of the Order of Loyalty to the Crown of Malaysia]]\n[[Category:People of the Cold War]]\n", "name_user": "Livinius", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eGuillaume affair", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Willy_Brandt"}
{"title_page": "Guillermo Rodriguez (comedian)", "text_new": "{{other people||Guillermo Rodriguez (disambiguation)}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Guillermo Rodriguez\n| image = GuillermoD\u00edazHWOFJan2013.jpg\n| alt = \n| caption = Rodriguez in January 2013\n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1971|01|27}}\n| birth_place = [[Zacatecas City]], [[Mexico]]{{Citation needed|date=June 2019}}\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| nationality = Mexican/American\n| other_names = \n| occupation = TV personality, security guard, comedian \n| years_active = 2003-present\n| known_for = ''[[Jimmy Kimmel Live!]]''\n}}\n\n'''Guillermo Rodriguez'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://abc.go.com/shows/jimmy-kimmel-live/cast/guillermo|title=Guillermo Rodriguez {{!}} Jimmy Kimmel Live!|website=ABC|access-date=2017-09-15}}</ref> (born January 27, 1971), more commonly known as '''Guillermo''', is a Mexican-American<ref>{{cite web | title='Jimmy Kimmel' Star Guillermo Responds to Donald Trump's Anti-Mexico Comments With Hilarious Bilingual Bit | website=The Hollywood Reporter | url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/jimmy-kimmel-star-guillermo-donald-805056 | access-date=2019-12-25}}</ref> [[talk show]] personality who rose to fame while working as a parking lot [[security guard]] at the [[Hollywood Boulevard]] studios for American late night talk show ''[[Jimmy Kimmel Live!]]''.<ref name=latimes/> He continues in character and title as ''Jimmy Kimmel Live!''{{'}}s security guard, but actually performs nightly as [[Jimmy Kimmel]]'s [[sidekick]].\n\n==Life and career==\n{{Original research|part=section|date=February 2018}}\nRodriguez was born in [[Zacatecas, Zacatecas|Zacatecas]], [[Mexico]].{{Citation needed|date=February 2018}} He became a permanent, nightly cast-member on ''Jimmy Kimmel Live!'' after performing in comedy segments written for the show. His broken English coupled with his affability and Teddy Bear-like quality have earned him a high-profile supporting role as a personality on the show. Guillermo took over main red-carpet interviewing duties in 2011 from the late [[Frank Potenza|\"Uncle Frank\" Potenza]], whom he was often paired with for the show's comedic skits.<ref name=\"latimes\">{{cite news|first=|last=|title=Passings: Frank Potenza, John Howard Davies, Jack Layton |url=http://articles.latimes.com/2011/aug/24/local/la-me-passings-20110824 |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |publisher= |date=2011-08-24|accessdate=2011-09-01}}</ref>\n\nRodriguez's signature segment is \"Guillermo's Hollywood Roundup\", in which, dressed in a cowboy outfit and pretending to twirl a special effect operated lasso, he makes a mockery of entertainment news shows featured widely on television. From outside the theater and standing next to his [[West Coast Customs]]-made \"Guillermobile\", he answers Kimmel's questions about the latest [[Tabloid (newspaper format)|tabloid]] stories by taking a rack of magazines that the \"Guillermobile\" has been fitted with, and attempts to interpret the stories in an amusing and mis-translated way.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20110303134240/http://abc.go.com/shows/jimmy-kimmel-live/bio/guillermo-rodriguez/637042 Guillermo's bio] at [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]].com</ref>\n\nAnother recurring joke is announcing that Rodriguez has a role in a current or recent major motion picture release and showing a clip of an at-first familiar trailer for the movie with Rodriguez edited in, his appearance often made-up to resemble a character in the movie. One sketch has Rodriguez impersonating [[Matt Damon]]'s character of [[Jason Bourne]] in ''[[The Bourne Ultimatum (film) |The Bourne Ultimatum]]'' by responding when asked to be named, \"I am Yay-son... Bourne Identity.\" A physical fight between Rodriguez and Damon's actual character ensues. Rodriguez also starred alongside Kimmel in Boo!, a spoof of [[Saw (franchise)|''Saw'']].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dreadcentral.com/news/34146/watch-jimmy-kimmels-saw-vi-spoof-boo|title=More Campers Are Left 2 Die - Dread Central|date=29 May 2012|publisher=}}</ref> \n\nRodriguez often sets out to interview famous celebrities. Some of his subjects do not know who he is, which the show uses for humorous interplay. Rodriguez regularly appears at the [[NBA Finals]] to interview players. At the [[2015 NBA Finals|2015 Finals]], he called out to [[LeBron James]] as James was practicing. James ignored Rodriguez, who had a meter counting how many times the name \"LeBron\" would be called before James acknowledged his presence.\n\nRodriguez appeared as a special guest on the last episode of [[Univision]] [[telenovela]] [[Eva Luna (soap opera)|''Eva Luna'']] on April 11, 2011. In 2017, he had a brief uncredited role in [[Marvel Entertainment|Marvel]]'s ''[[Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2]]'' as a policeman, which he revealed in a video on ''Jimmy Kimmel Live!'' in April 2017.<ref name=\"Guillermo in Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=45TAnT9XDvk|title=Guillermo in Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2|first=|last=Jimmy Kimmel Live|date=13 April 2017|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n\nRodriguez was made an [[Honorary citizenship|honorary citizen]] of [[Dildo, Newfoundland and Labrador|Dildo]] through the [[Newfoundland and Labrador|Newfoundland]] tradition of \"screeching in,\" on August 15, 2019 during ''Jimmy Kimmel Live!'' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wK3HWT7NIN4|title=Jimmy Kimmel - Mayor of Dildo!|website=Youtube|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-16}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n!colspan=\"4\" style=\"background: LightSteelBlue;\"|Film\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n!Notes\n|-\n|2009\n|''[[Rock Slyde]]''\n|Gary\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2]]''\n|Cop #2, uncredited\n|<ref name=\"Guillermo in Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2\" />\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[The Little Mermaid Live!]]''\n|Dat Blowfish\n|\n|}\n\n== Broadway Acts ==\n\nMarket Cart Seller in Aladdin\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{imdb name|2281865|Guillermo Rodriguez}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rodriguez, Guillermo}}\n[[Category:1971 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Mexican television personalities]]\n[[Category:Mexican emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:Security guards]]\n[[Category:American television personalities of Mexican descent]]\n[[Category:People with acquired American citizenship]]\n", "text_old": "{{other people||Guillermo Rodriguez (disambiguation)}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Guillermo Rodriguez\n| image = GuillermoD\u00edazHWOFJan2013.jpg\n| alt = \n| caption = Rodriguez in January 2013\n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1971|01|27}}\n| birth_place = [[Zacatecas City]], [[Mexico]]{{Citation needed|date=June 2019}}\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| nationality = Mexican/American\n| other_names = \n| occupation = TV personality, security guard, comedian \n| years_active = 2003-present\n| known_for = ''[[Jimmy Kimmel Live!]]''\n}}\n\n'''Guillermo Rodriguez'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://abc.go.com/shows/jimmy-kimmel-live/cast/guillermo|title=Guillermo Rodriguez {{!}} Jimmy Kimmel Live!|website=ABC|access-date=2017-09-15}}</ref> (born January 27, 1971), more commonly known as '''Guillermo''', is a Mexican-American<ref>{{cite web | title='Jimmy Kimmel' Star Guillermo Responds to Donald Trump's Anti-Mexico Comments With Hilarious Bilingual Bit | website=The Hollywood Reporter | url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/jimmy-kimmel-star-guillermo-donald-805056 | access-date=2019-12-25}}</ref> [[talk show]] personality who rose to fame while working as a parking lot [[security guard]] at the [[Hollywood Boulevard]] studios for American late night talk show ''[[Jimmy Kimmel Live!]]''.<ref name=latimes/> He continues in character and title as ''Jimmy Kimmel Live!''{{'}}s security guard, but actually performs nightly as [[Jimmy Kimmel]]'s [[sidekick]].\n\n==Life and career==\n{{Original research|part=section|date=February 2018}}\nRodriguez was born in [[Zacatecas, Zacatecas|Zacatecas]], [[Mexico]].{{Citation needed|date=February 2018}} He became a permanent, nightly cast-member on ''Jimmy Kimmel Live!'' after performing in comedy segments written for the show. His broken English coupled with his affability and Teddy Bear-like quality have earned him a high-profile supporting role as a personality on the show. Guillermo took over main red-carpet interviewing duties in 2011 from the late [[Frank Potenza|\"Uncle Frank\" Potenza]], whom he was often paired with for the show's comedic skits.<ref name=\"latimes\">{{cite news|first=|last=|title=Passings: Frank Potenza, John Howard Davies, Jack Layton |url=http://articles.latimes.com/2011/aug/24/local/la-me-passings-20110824 |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |publisher= |date=2011-08-24|accessdate=2011-09-01}}</ref>\n\nRodriguez's signature segment is \"Guillermo's Hollywood Roundup\", in which, dressed in a cowboy outfit and pretending to twirl a special effect operated lasso, he makes a mockery of entertainment news shows featured widely on television. From outside the theater and standing next to his [[West Coast Customs]]-made \"Guillermobile\", he answers Kimmel's questions about the latest [[Tabloid (newspaper format)|tabloid]] stories by taking a rack of magazines that the \"Guillermobile\" has been fitted with, and attempts to interpret the stories in an amusing and mis-translated way.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20110303134240/http://abc.go.com/shows/jimmy-kimmel-live/bio/guillermo-rodriguez/637042 Guillermo's bio] at [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]].com</ref>\n\nAnother recurring joke is announcing that Rodriguez has a role in a current or recent major motion picture release and showing a clip of an at-first familiar trailer for the movie with Rodriguez edited in, his appearance